p: From 2011 to 2015, new HIV diagnosis rates attributed to heterosexual contact were significantly higher in women born in Oceania (IRR 5.43, 95% CI 3.73–7.92), Southern and Eastern Europe (IRR 2.10, 95% CI 1.22–3.61), North Africa and the Middle East (IRR 8.15, 95% CI 5.30–12.52), South-East Asia (IRR 8.91, 95% CI 6.72–11.81) and Sub-Saharan Africa (IRR 38.21, 95% CI 29.68–49.19) than in Australian-born women. Rates were not significantly different for other regions of birth.
